news.title: NGT stops Tamil Nadu housing board flats' construction in Chennai
news.para: TNHB has proposed to construct three 19-storeyed blocks with 304 residential units and a commercial complex. Environmental clearance (EC) for this project was sanctioned by the state-level environment impact assessment authority (SEIAA) in January.

news.title: Caretaker has no claim on a property regardless of long possession: SC
news.para: The SC set aside the order of a trial court and high court which had refused to allow a plea of an owner for not proceeding on a suit filed by a caretaker seeking that he be not vacated from the premises.

news.title: RBI allows banks to sell fraud NPAs to asset reconstruction companies
news.para: Banks are targeting to sell Rs 2 lakh crore worth of NPAs to the bad bank or the National Asset Reconstruction Company (NARCL) for recovery. However, they have hit a roadblock in respect of accounts that have been classified as fraud, as they were not allowed to sell them.

news.title: NBCC bags Rs 968 crore contract in Maldives to construct 2,000 flats
news.para: In a regulatory filing, NBCC informed that it has secured the work order of construction of 2000 Social Housing at Hulhumale, Maldives on EPC basis. "The total cost of the project is USD 130 Million (Rs 968.50 crore approx)," it added.

news.title: Noida authority cuts transfer charges by half for residential plots
news.para: Residential plot owners and flat buyers entering the secondary market will have to pay 2.5% as charges now instead of 5%. Similarly transfer charges for other categories — commercial, industrial and institutional — have also been revised.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing Finance sells stake worth Rs 251 crore in OakNorth
news.para: ​"Indiabulls Housing Finance Ltd has sold a portion of its stake in OakNorth Holdings Ltd (the wholly owning parent company of OakNorth Bank plc) for approximately Rs 251 crore.

news.title: SIT seeks more time to submit report on Supertech Emerald Court case
news.para: More than 40 employees were instrumental in amending the building maps of the twin towers that came up in the violation of the building bylaws.

news.title: Retail investors top priority, says crisis-hit Evergrande
news.para: Hui Ka Yan’s statement came after the developer said on Wednesday it had “resolved” a coupon payment on an onshore bond, pushing the company’s stock price to its biggest single-day percentage rise since its listing in 2009.

news.title: For Xi Jinping and China Evergrande, a delicate balancing act
news.para: Evergrande's borrow-to-build model was enabled by a government reliant on property sales for revenue and unwilling to bite the bullet on runaway indebtedness for fear a collapse in prices would have devastating consequences for a country in which property accounts for 40% of household wealth.

news.title: Anjani Logistics acquires 4-acre land at MIHAN to build housing, commercial complex
news.para: It said Mahindra, Moraj and NITPL have developed their residential projects within MIHAN. Tech giant HCL has also acquired about 20 acres of land at MIHAN for staff quarters. This has resulted in the availability of about 5,000 to 7,000 houses in the recent future.

news.title: China Evergrande's bondholders in limbo over debt crisis
news.para: Evergrande appointed financial advisers and warned of default last week, and world markets fell heavily on Monday amid fears of contagion, though they have since stabilised.

news.title: Alarmed by Evergrande, China's lenders hold back on new credit for builders
news.para: Evergrande's problems will pile pressure on peers to access funding, and analysts have warned that if property developers are unable to pay investors, suppliers and lenders China's financial system could go into shock.

news.title: Fears of global shockwaves from China Evergrande Group's debts ease
news.para: But economists said while Chinese banks and other creditors are likely to suffer losses, there appeared to be little way a default on its 2 trillion yuan (USD 310 billion) in debt would hurt the Chinese system or feed through to financial markets abroad.

news.title: More than one lakh PMAY houses built in one month in Madhya Pradesh
news.para: The panchayat and rural development department has been executing the PM rural housing scheme since April 2016 in the state. Of the total target of 26.28 lakh houses in MP, 20.65 lakh houses have already been constructed.

news.title: Dalmia Cement adds 2.25 MTPA capacity with an investment of Rs 325 crore
news.para: ​​It has made an investment of Rs 325 crore for this addition, the company said in a media release. With this addition, Dalmia Cement (Bharat)’s overall capacity at the plant has now gone up to 3.95 million tons per annum.
